From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 09:46:00 +0800
Subject: Disable AutomationControlled Blink feature for renderer processes

When BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK) is set, automatically disable the
AutomationControlled Blink runtime-enabled feature for all renderer
processes. This forces navigator.webdriver to return false and hides
the automation signal from JavaScript detection scripts, even if
--enable-automation is set at the browser level.

---
 chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc b/chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc
index abcdef1..abcdef2 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc
@@ -2898,6 +2898,11 @@
     }
 #endif

+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+    command_line->AppendSwitchASCII(switches::kDisableBlinkFeatures,
+                                    "AutomationControlled");
+#endif
+
     MaybeCopyDisableWebRtcEncryptionSwitch(command_line, browser_command_line,
                                            chrome::GetChannel());
     if (process) {
